Frosty's Picks I have major hearing problems. It’s called tinnitus and for those of you who don’t know it is a constant ringing in your ears. Therefore, it is hard for me to find audience shows that are of good enough quality for me to listen to without doing further damage to my ears by having to turn up the volume.  I am not saying anything about these shows except that as a person with major hearing lose, these are some of the shows that I have on my I-Pod.  I am not giving any of these shows a review. I can always find something good in every show…...as long as I can hear it!!!!Here is my list, by date, for today 9/19/08;

7.6.84         10.15.84      6.19.91     
7.18.89        6.21.84       9.6.85   
10.12.84       10.12.83      11.1.85

Please let me know if you have any show suggestions that compare to these in quality of sound.
Peace,
Frosty

Day 2 of THE GOOD OLE' GRATEFUL DEAD! As i mentioned in the 7/17/89 review(Green Mt.Boys Recording) this was my 1st Dead Experience. Upon this morn, I was buying a pack of 'Boro's and a Snickers at a Canteen tent when all of a sudden I hear,"Hey Teeroy", I turned around and there was my best friend, I had left back in Missouri,standing there! man! MY o.b.e kicked in heavy. He saw my pigpenesque patches n pins, denim jacket and just knew it ws me he was chortling to. For the next two days we just laughed,giggled and wiggled to the Boyz', who were SMOKIN' HOT ALL THROUGH THE 3 DAYS IN THE VALLEY. Short of a Dark Star, this 3 day run was packked full of their hits and gosh was the versions just mind-boggling as I look back at it all in humble, thankful retrospect. Thank you Karl and Sharon and Thank You, Jerry,Phil,Bill,Bobby,Mickey and Brent.!! Peace from thaaaa....TyeDyeGuy.
